04:27.205 --> 04:28.656
BETH: <i>What's going on, honey?</i>

04:30.289 --> 04:32.172
My mom doesn't know I'm here.

04:33.930 --> 04:37.039
We're past due on our gas.

04:38.463 --> 04:40.625
We haven't had heat
in a couple of weeks.

04:42.260 --> 04:45.562
We need $89.34.

04:48.028 --> 04:49.687
I didn't know where else to go.

04:50.601 --> 04:51.867
It's okay.

04:52.695 --> 04:56.125
Hey, uh, I'm gonna call your mom

04:56.632 --> 04:58.565
and I'm gonna set up a recurring
direct deposit until...

04:58.600 --> 05:01.068
- Randall.
- No. She won't take it.

05:01.320 --> 05:03.109
Look, I don't need extra,

05:03.134 --> 05:06.240
but it needs to be cash
so I can tell her

05:06.265 --> 05:08.509
that I saved up my allowance
from when I was here.

05:09.675 --> 05:13.304
We need the heat back on before
Miss Linda does her next visit.

05:20.980 --> 05:23.304
(RANDALL SNIFFS, SIGHS)

05:28.968 --> 05:30.875
Come on. I'll give you a ride home.

05:31.289 --> 05:32.584
I won't come up.

05:32.609 --> 05:34.234
But you got to promise me
something, Deja.

05:34.796 --> 05:36.403
If something like this
ever happens again,

05:36.437 --> 05:39.881
or if you need anything,
you call us, okay?

05:39.906 --> 05:42.726
You don't wait for the heat
to go off. You call us.

05:46.043 --> 05:47.218
Come on.

05:52.117 --> 05:53.515
BETH: The girls are at your mom's.

05:53.540 --> 05:55.601
Everything I own with glitter is packed.

05:55.789 --> 05:58.382
It is T-minus 30 minutes to departure.

05:58.617 --> 06:00.007
Vegas, baby!

06:01.421 --> 06:02.600
- Hey.
- Hmm?

06:02.625 --> 06:04.197
Where are the neat piles organized by

06:04.232 --> 06:05.851
size, color and material, man?

06:05.991 --> 06:08.765
- Maybe we shouldn't go.
- Huh? What?

06:08.804 --> 06:11.154
No. You can't bail
on Toby's bachelor party.

06:11.179 --> 06:13.271
And I can't bail
on Kate's bachelorette, so...

06:13.296 --> 06:15.350
Look, what if Deja needs us

06:15.375 --> 06:16.914
and we're on the other side
of the country?

06:16.939 --> 06:19.459
Hey. It's been weeks. She hasn't called.

06:19.484 --> 06:21.281
Okay? That's a good thing.

06:21.875 --> 06:23.662
That means her mom is doing good.

06:23.687 --> 06:27.109
And if she's not, then
Linda will step in, you know?

06:27.476 --> 06:30.140
That's all we can do, or we're
gonna drive ourselves crazy.

06:30.577 --> 06:33.054
Okay? It is what it is.

06:34.601 --> 06:35.804
Okay.

06:36.007 --> 06:39.781
All right? Now, come on.
Baby, you love Vegas.

06:40.109 --> 06:41.529
Do <i>Rain Man</i> blackjack for me.

06:41.554 --> 06:43.656
I don't feel like doing
<i>Rain Man</i> blackjack.

06:43.760 --> 06:44.937
Okay.

06:46.804 --> 06:48.757
You know we're pity invites, right?

06:49.023 --> 06:50.978
Nobody wants their
brother- or sister-in-law

06:51.012 --> 06:52.773
watching them go wild in Vegas.

06:52.798 --> 06:55.048
Hey. I'm totally down
with a pity invite, okay?

06:55.083 --> 06:56.960
I deserve a pity invite.

06:56.985 --> 06:59.786
I have two children,
work a full-time job,

06:59.821 --> 07:01.822
and manage a tenement,

07:01.856 --> 07:04.057
because you saw a mural
and imagined a cat.

07:04.552 --> 07:06.484
Hey, I deserve this.

07:09.921 --> 07:11.999
Definitely have a 16 against a nine.

07:12.033 --> 07:15.102
- Definitely gonna hit. 16 plus five is 21.
- (LAUGHS)

07:15.136 --> 07:16.436
It's definitely a winning hand.

07:16.471 --> 07:18.071
- Definitely a winning hand.
- (LAUGHING)

07:18.296 --> 07:19.742
- (POUNDING THE BED)
- Vegas, baby!

07:20.015 --> 07:21.148
Vegas!

07:22.984 --> 07:25.145
MADISON: It's a live <i>Magic Mike</i> show.

07:25.179 --> 07:26.710
Like the movie but in real life.

07:26.735 --> 07:29.734
They say it's like literally
being inside of <i>Magic Mike.</i>

07:29.759 --> 07:32.783
Hm, Madison, I don't know. I don't
know. Like, what's all the oil and...

07:32.808 --> 07:34.006
- TOBY: Hey, hon.
- Yeah.

07:34.031 --> 07:36.323
I was just... Oh. Madison's here, again.

07:36.357 --> 07:37.820
Hey, Toblerone.

07:38.343 --> 07:39.585
I really don't like that.

07:39.610 --> 07:43.330
Uh, I'm packing for
this Vegas bromance-a-thon,

07:43.364 --> 07:45.335
and I'm trying to figure out if I go

07:45.523 --> 07:48.820
Clooney <i>Ocean</i> or Sinatra <i>Ocean.</i>

07:48.929 --> 07:51.859
- Hmm.
- I need fiancée wisdom.

07:52.718 --> 07:53.937
Toby.

07:55.100 --> 07:56.835
You're a thief and a liar.

07:58.187 --> 07:59.880
I only lied about being a thief.

08:01.492 --> 08:03.101
Yep, you're right. Clooney <i>Ocean.</i>

08:03.317 --> 08:05.652
You're always right. I like it.
That's why I put a ring on it.

08:05.687 --> 08:07.387
MADISON: You guys are so <i>Mike and Molly,</i>

08:07.422 --> 08:09.835
- I can't stand it.
- (WHISPERS): I hate you so much.

08:10.414 --> 08:11.976
Okay, I am out.

08:12.992 --> 08:14.828
Kate, I will see you at the airport.

08:14.968 --> 08:16.788
Don't stress. I'm all over this.

08:16.813 --> 08:18.132
That's what I'm stressed about.

08:18.157 --> 08:19.632
Later, Toby Bryant!

08:19.657 --> 08:21.458
You know what?
You got to stop doing that,

08:21.483 --> 08:22.828
'cause that's... (SIGHS)

08:24.101 --> 08:26.140
You know, I like Toby Bryant.
That's good.

08:26.421 --> 08:27.718
What's going on? You okay?

08:27.743 --> 08:30.078
- Yeah. Come on.
- Yeah?

08:31.007 --> 08:32.109
Joint belly rub?

08:32.134 --> 08:35.375
- You or the dog?
- Uh, dog first. Come here, buddy.

08:35.547 --> 08:37.967
- Flip it. Flipper pup.
- (KATE LAUGHS)

08:38.960 --> 08:41.000
I wish we were doing
our Vegas parties together.

08:41.025 --> 08:43.842
Me, too. But that's exactly why
we should be doing them apart.

08:43.868 --> 08:47.042
Because we are wildly
codependent, all right?

08:47.077 --> 08:49.778
I had to scrape the bottom
of a very nerdy friend barrel

08:49.813 --> 08:51.125
to even have a bachelor party.

08:51.150 --> 08:53.916
Madison is running point on yours,

08:53.950 --> 08:55.703
for God's sake. Madison.

08:55.976 --> 08:57.687
Well, at least you get Randall at yours.

08:57.712 --> 08:59.947
- Randall can make anything fun.
- Yeah, he can.

08:59.972 --> 09:01.726
At least I... that's how I remember it,

09:01.751 --> 09:04.421
when I actually, you know,
used to see him.

09:04.446 --> 09:07.796
And I get Beth, who I've spent
a sum total of seven minutes

09:07.831 --> 09:09.523
alone with my entire life.

09:09.548 --> 09:11.585
- Come on, Beth is great.
- Okay, you take her.

09:11.610 --> 09:13.695
- And I'll take Randall.
- Oh, no-no-no-no-no.

09:13.720 --> 09:15.804
The Brothers Pearson
are all mine this weekend.

09:15.829 --> 09:17.937
I got one scoop
of dark chocolate Pearson,

09:18.023 --> 09:20.125
and one scoop of creamy vanilla Pearson,

09:20.150 --> 09:21.750
and I'm gonna be the ruddy strawberry

09:21.775 --> 09:24.046
that brings it all together, baby.

09:26.082 --> 09:26.975
(TOBY SIGHS)

09:27.000 --> 09:29.015
I'm sorry that your
brother couldn't make it.

09:29.375 --> 09:30.921
Yeah, well, that's an understatement.

09:30.946 --> 09:33.625
He had a hundred excuses before
I even got the question out.

09:33.699 --> 09:36.242
But good news is
we'll be back here in no time,

09:36.267 --> 09:38.937
- laying in bed with this big fella.
- (CHUCKLES)

09:38.962 --> 09:41.625
Huh? Recounting our Vegas war stories.

09:42.101 --> 09:44.148
- (LAUGHS)
- Huh? And then we won't have to have

09:44.173 --> 09:47.742
another external relationship
for at least another year.

09:49.468 --> 09:51.273
(SIGHS) See, you always
know what to say.

09:51.308 --> 09:53.209
Yeah. All right. (CLEARS THROAT)

09:53.243 --> 09:55.054
Scoot that. My turn.

09:55.664 --> 09:57.546
- (SIGHS) Oh.
- What, what?

09:57.571 --> 09:58.872
- Right here? Right here?
- (TOBY PANTING)

09:59.125 --> 10:04.226
synced and corrected by susinz
*www.addic7ed.com*

10:13.109 --> 10:15.710
All right, Katie girl,
what shape should I try?

10:15.945 --> 10:17.687
Mm, Texas.

10:17.851 --> 10:18.929
Texas.

10:18.954 --> 10:20.093
Okay.

10:20.497 --> 10:21.953
- Dad.
- Yeah.

10:22.046 --> 10:24.328
Aren't you supposed to do
special stuff today

10:24.353 --> 10:26.488
to show Mom that you
love her, or whatever?

10:26.726 --> 10:29.757
We're taking the year off
from the special stuff,

10:29.782 --> 10:31.953
but I love your mom always.

10:31.978 --> 10:33.515
But you always do something.

10:33.540 --> 10:35.976
Yeah, I know. I'm just,
I'm not allowed to this year.

10:37.757 --> 10:40.539
- What if we did something for you guys?
- KATE AND RANDALL: Yeah!

10:40.564 --> 10:42.971
- Huh?
- We'd do everything. We promise.

10:44.304 --> 10:46.296
Okay, so if you do everything,

10:46.321 --> 10:48.218
then technically
I'm not breaking the rules.

10:48.243 --> 10:50.531
- Okay, what'd you have in mind?
- Uh, we'll make dinner.

10:50.953 --> 10:53.154
- (KIDS CHATTERING EXCITEDLY)
- Hey. What is going on?

10:53.179 --> 10:55.093
- What are you guys conspiring about?
- (JACK CLEARS THROAT)

10:55.118 --> 10:57.226
We're gonna throw you guys
a big anniversary party!

10:57.251 --> 10:58.773
- KEVIN: Yeah!
- KATE: Yay!

10:59.945 --> 11:01.190
I'm ready for pancakes!

11:01.224 --> 11:02.414
- RANDALL: Me, too!
- KEVIN: With chocolate chips!

11:02.439 --> 11:03.500
- I...
- REBECCA: Jack.

11:03.525 --> 11:04.687
No. Wasn't me.

11:05.762 --> 11:06.862
Yes!

11:06.896 --> 11:07.929
(HORN HONKS)

11:08.725 --> 11:09.968
Damn, baby!

11:09.993 --> 11:12.539
I am feeling Vegas right now!

11:12.804 --> 11:13.904
Let's do something crazy.

11:13.929 --> 11:15.437
- Let's go skydiving.
- Okay.

11:15.482 --> 11:17.890
Oh, let's go take Ecstasy and
see the magician that got ate

11:17.915 --> 11:20.093
- by the lion.
- I think I'm just gonna call Deja.

11:20.289 --> 11:21.781
Real quick. Let her know we're in Vegas.

11:21.806 --> 11:22.742
Hey, hey.

11:22.767 --> 11:25.781
- Just...
- No, no, no. This is a Deja-free zone.

11:25.815 --> 11:28.445
Um, what if she comes to
the house and we're not there?

11:28.703 --> 11:30.445
Randall, are you serious?

11:31.781 --> 11:32.843
Sorry.

11:34.407 --> 11:37.703
I guess I just can't,
what, detach like you can.

11:38.203 --> 11:41.109
- Detach?
- Come on, man, cut me some slack.

11:41.134 --> 11:43.140
You know you're the head, I'm the heart.

11:45.941 --> 11:49.060
Deja's no longer
a part of our home, okay?

11:49.085 --> 11:53.008
It's not fair to anyone involved
to keep acting like she is.

11:53.042 --> 11:54.382
You know that.

11:55.966 --> 11:57.070
Yeah.

11:58.710 --> 12:00.015
Yeah, you're right.

12:00.446 --> 12:03.117
Well, the head is always right, I guess.

12:05.414 --> 12:08.140
I said you were able to detach
from this Deja situation,

12:08.165 --> 12:09.992
- not that you were detached.
- Yep.

12:11.320 --> 12:13.028
Calling you the head was a compliment.

12:13.062 --> 12:14.696
I meant it as a compliment.

12:14.731 --> 12:16.414
Thank you for the compliment.

12:20.069 --> 12:21.250
(SIGHS)

12:26.657 --> 12:27.874
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

12:29.804 --> 12:31.429
- Fresh towels.
- Come on in.

12:31.570 --> 12:34.281
I didn't just call you in here
for fresh towels. I, uh...

12:34.306 --> 12:35.410
I want to show you something.

12:35.435 --> 12:36.656
- And what's your name?
- Renata.

12:36.681 --> 12:38.992
Renata. Look at this right here.
You know what that is?

12:39.125 --> 12:41.140
There's 27 bottles of alcohol in there.

12:41.382 --> 12:43.125
Since I was 18,
I've been to Vegas probably...

12:43.159 --> 12:44.593
I don't know... 50 times.

12:44.618 --> 12:46.304
And of those 50 times,
I want you to guess

12:46.329 --> 12:48.648
how many I've been
absolutely blackout drunk for.

12:48.965 --> 12:50.679
- All of them.
- All of them. Yes.

12:50.785 --> 12:51.879
Every single one of 'em.

12:51.914 --> 12:53.984
Good job. You're good at this
game. How did you know that?

12:54.054 --> 12:55.976
You're Rehab Manny who got drunk

12:56.001 --> 12:58.011
and ran over his daughter with a car.

12:59.265 --> 13:01.289
Renata, you can't believe
everything you read.

13:01.314 --> 13:04.500
But, anyway, uh, coming to Vegas
at this point in my life

13:04.525 --> 13:08.382
is like, um... it's like
my Mount Everest, okay?

13:08.599 --> 13:10.031
And I'm gonna conquer it.

13:10.234 --> 13:12.648
So, tomorrow,
when you come in here, right,

13:12.673 --> 13:14.960
you're gonna walk over here,
you're gonna count 27 bottles

13:14.985 --> 13:17.000
of unopened alcohol,
you're gonna reach over here,

13:17.025 --> 13:19.820
you're gonna grab that $100 tip
that I'm leaving for <i>you,</i>

13:19.845 --> 13:22.460
and you're gonna feel so good
about being part

13:22.485 --> 13:24.351
of this stranger's journey, all right?

13:24.578 --> 13:27.671
The, uh, the Rehab Manny,
as you so lovingly called him,

13:27.708 --> 13:32.779
that you witnessed conquer
his personal Mount Everest.

13:33.976 --> 13:35.726
Do you still want towels?

13:38.484 --> 13:39.695
(EXHALES) Sure.

13:39.908 --> 13:42.625
♪ <i>Say, say, say, hey, hey now, baby</i> ♪

13:44.255 --> 13:45.835
♪ <i>Oh, Mama, don't play now...</i> ♪

13:45.860 --> 13:48.671
- Beth! You made it!
- Hey! Yeah, we just got in.

13:51.328 --> 13:52.359
Do you want to come in?

13:52.384 --> 13:53.953
- Yeah.
- Okay. (CHUCKLES)

13:53.978 --> 13:55.750
Ah, Randall! My main man!

13:55.775 --> 13:57.218
- How you doing? I'm all right.
- Boom!

13:57.243 --> 13:58.757
These are my girls from
the support group.

13:58.782 --> 14:01.656
- It's Liz, and this is Laurie.
- Nice to meet you. Beth.

14:01.681 --> 14:03.507
- Gorgeous.
- This is, uh, Shooter.

14:03.532 --> 14:05.648
- How you doing? Pleasure.
- We got Rick and Stu, my stud buds

14:05.673 --> 14:07.015
- from the I.T. office.
- What up, Rick?

14:07.040 --> 14:09.367
- Stu! Sorry! This is Rick. Pleasure.
- Bill.

14:10.593 --> 14:12.039
- (WOMEN GASPING)
- And there she is.

14:12.064 --> 14:13.726
This is Madison, the mastermind.

14:13.751 --> 14:16.085
- Oh. You did all this?
- I've been dying to meet you!

14:16.398 --> 14:17.781
- Come here. Give me a hug.
- Oh!

14:17.806 --> 14:20.257
- Hey-o! Here we are!
- Oh! Think you know that guy.

14:20.282 --> 14:21.562
- How you doing, bro?
- Good. You?

14:21.587 --> 14:23.632
- I'm doing well, thanks.
- All right. Good to see you.

14:23.657 --> 14:25.412
- Celebrating this guy.
- You know what, can I?

14:25.437 --> 14:27.015
- Yeah.
- You mind if I get in here?

14:27.040 --> 14:28.906
When Kate sent out the guest
list, I followed you on Insta.

14:28.931 --> 14:32.148
Your hair is always different,
and I am obsessed.

14:32.424 --> 14:34.828
Girls, I've got party gifts.

14:35.304 --> 14:36.593
- (RANDALL GROWLS, CHUCKLES)
- Look at these guys.

14:36.618 --> 14:38.919
- Modern day Rat Pack, huh?
- Hey!

14:38.944 --> 14:40.578
I'm-I'm not ready.

14:40.649 --> 14:41.929
- Ah!
- (LAUGHTER)

14:44.259 --> 14:46.179
Classy. (CHUCKLES) Literary.

14:46.264 --> 14:48.554
- To Toby!
- ALL: Toby! (WHOOPING)

14:49.060 --> 14:51.195
- To Kate!
- ALL: To Kate!

14:53.302 --> 14:56.375
Oh, straight from the bottle.
Okay. Straight from the bottle.

14:57.228 --> 14:59.546
What's <i>Herbes de Provence?</i>

15:01.148 --> 15:02.226
I don't know, bud.

15:02.251 --> 15:04.984
But are you sure you just
don't want to make spaghetti

15:05.009 --> 15:08.195
- or something?
- Didn't Mom say at Kate's piano recital

15:08.220 --> 15:10.484
that she always wanted
to try Cornish hens?

15:12.233 --> 15:13.382
She did.

15:13.697 --> 15:15.398
Then get in the game, Dad.

15:16.075 --> 15:17.453
(GROANS SOFTLY)

15:22.656 --> 15:24.601
- Just stick with me, kid.
- BOY: Hey, Randall.

15:24.626 --> 15:26.585
Andrew, Bryce, in my hood.

15:27.261 --> 15:28.484
♪

15:43.840 --> 15:47.570
Hey, where are you guys gonna be
doing this top secret research?

15:47.595 --> 15:49.640
- Research station is in the back.
- Okay.

15:49.665 --> 15:51.818
- Come on, Kate!
- Well, find me if you need any help.

15:51.852 --> 15:52.945
Okay, Mom!

15:53.076 --> 15:54.242
(CHUCKLES)

15:55.484 --> 15:57.234
TOBY: Hey, so I'm thinking,
after we settle up here,

15:57.259 --> 16:00.242
we hit the "clurb," and then,
uh, and then maybe we go do

16:00.267 --> 16:01.851
some gambling down in gritty Old Vegas,

16:01.876 --> 16:03.117
- like in <i>Swingers.</i>
<i>- Yeah!</i>

16:03.142 --> 16:06.109
'Cause the Strip is hip,
but downtown is where it's at.

16:06.851 --> 16:08.257
Something else to drink, gentlemen?

16:08.282 --> 16:10.773
I will do another soda water
with a lime, please.

16:10.921 --> 16:13.072
TOBY: I'm all set. Thanks.
- Uh, I'm good...

16:13.640 --> 16:15.498
Uh, hey, listen, thanks for coming out.

16:15.523 --> 16:17.310
I-I know this alcohol thing
can be kind of...

16:17.344 --> 16:18.773
No, don't worry about it.
Don't worry about it.

16:18.798 --> 16:20.375
- It's fine. Thank you.
- Okay.

16:20.881 --> 16:23.828
Oh, guys, check this out.
Randall's bachelor party,

16:23.853 --> 16:25.671
- which I was in charge of, okay...
- ALL: Ooh!

16:25.696 --> 16:28.460
It's fine. I'm gonna tell the
story. So, I bring him to this,

16:28.485 --> 16:30.499
uh, this pretty seedy
strip club, you know,

16:30.524 --> 16:31.710
- to make a man out of him, right?
- (CHUCKLING)

16:31.735 --> 16:32.992
That's what you do. I'm his brother.

16:33.128 --> 16:36.007
Uh, we get there, and Randall,

16:36.135 --> 16:38.859
within 20 minutes, has
convinced two of the strippers

16:39.082 --> 16:41.164
to quit their jobs
and go back to school.

16:41.189 --> 16:42.394
(LAUGHTER)

16:42.419 --> 16:44.370
- He takes care of other people.
- I appreciate it.

16:44.405 --> 16:46.656
You know what, at-at least
I didn't date one of 'em

16:46.681 --> 16:48.207
- for a year.
- ALL: Ooh!

16:48.242 --> 16:50.101
It was... it was nice.

16:50.126 --> 16:52.311
- She was really sweet. She...
- (TOBY GUFFAWS)

16:52.346 --> 16:53.695
- She was a sweetheart.
- I bet it was.

16:53.720 --> 16:55.039
See, what you are witnessing here

16:55.064 --> 16:57.296
is the Kevin/Randall rivalry.

16:57.321 --> 16:59.148
It is a tale as old as time.

16:59.173 --> 17:00.281
(LAUGHTER)

17:00.835 --> 17:02.355
RANDALL: I didn't know
you knew about it.

17:02.389 --> 17:03.726
Whoa, whoa, whoa, that's
one of my costars.

17:03.751 --> 17:04.976
- Oh!
- That's one of my costars.

17:05.001 --> 17:06.531
I'm gonna go, uh,
I'm gonna go say hi. All right?

17:06.556 --> 17:07.608
Be right back.

17:11.515 --> 17:12.960
- So, Randall, hey...
- You know what, Tobe,

17:12.984 --> 17:14.522
I got to make a quick call.
I'll be right back.

17:14.548 --> 17:15.835
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

17:15.997 --> 17:17.789
(LAUGHTER, CHATTER CONTINUES)

17:21.694 --> 17:22.694
Emma.

17:22.720 --> 17:24.242
- Hey. How are you?
- Kevin. (CHUCKLES)

17:24.267 --> 17:26.828
- How you doing? Yeah?
- Hey. I'm good.

17:26.853 --> 17:28.987
- How are you?
- Really good, actually. I'm really good.

17:29.012 --> 17:30.945
- Good. That's really good.
- Thank you. Thanks.

17:31.009 --> 17:32.335
I heard about the rehab.

17:33.460 --> 17:34.804
(INHALES SHARPLY) Hollywood.

17:35.092 --> 17:36.914
- Where everyone's a mess!
- Right?

17:36.939 --> 17:38.156
- (LAUGHS)
- (LAUGHS)

17:38.476 --> 17:39.390
Yeah.

17:39.415 --> 17:42.684
I'm-I'm, uh, I'm looking forward
to <i>Hill 400</i> coming out.

17:42.709 --> 17:44.507
I'm actually counting down
the days until it's released.

17:44.532 --> 17:45.796
It's been a, uh...

17:46.834 --> 17:49.023
(DRAMATICALLY): "beacon of light
at the end of a very dark,

17:49.048 --> 17:50.281
very long year."

17:52.742 --> 17:53.953
You haven't heard?

17:54.671 --> 17:55.812
Haven't heard what?

17:55.837 --> 17:57.471
They cut me out of the movie.

17:57.775 --> 18:00.578
- Wait, they... I'm sorry...
- Ron sent a really nice note.

18:00.750 --> 18:03.359
Handwritten, so at least
I got a nice memento.

18:04.111 --> 18:05.523
He's, um... (CLEARS THROAT)

18:05.950 --> 18:07.656
he's going in a different direction.

18:08.133 --> 18:10.648
Said some characters just fell out,

18:10.673 --> 18:12.674
others were substantially cut down.

18:12.790 --> 18:15.109
I was in the "fell out" category.

18:16.054 --> 18:18.578
- Half my scenes were with you.
- Well, maybe you're in

18:18.603 --> 18:20.406
the "substantially cut down" category.

18:22.503 --> 18:23.914
Hey, let's have lunch soon.

18:26.540 --> 18:27.906
(DISTORTED ICE CLACKING)

18:28.208 --> 18:29.675
(DISTORTED CLINKING, LAUGHTER)

18:32.358 --> 18:33.843
BILL (DISTORTED):
Hey, Kevin, you coming back?

18:34.533 --> 18:35.695
Kevin? Hey.

18:36.343 --> 18:37.343
(CLEARLY): Kevin?

18:37.368 --> 18:39.168
- You coming back?
- Stu. How are you?

18:39.312 --> 18:40.843
Uh, Bill, but Stu's fine.

18:40.868 --> 18:43.523
- Um, anyway...
- Huh? Listen, can you, can you,

18:44.117 --> 18:45.421
- can you just do me a favor?
- Yeah.

18:45.446 --> 18:47.117
Can you tell Toby that I'm not,
I'm not feeling well?

18:47.142 --> 18:48.812
- I'm not, um...
- Oh.

18:49.914 --> 18:50.953
I'm gonna call it early.

18:50.978 --> 18:52.242
Can-can you, can you
tell him that for me?

18:52.267 --> 18:53.767
O-Okay. You're just not...

18:53.929 --> 18:55.156
Okay, um...

18:56.303 --> 18:57.320
RANDALL: <i>Deja.</i>

18:57.345 --> 18:59.031
It's Randall. I saw you called.

18:59.692 --> 19:01.187
DEJA: <i>Uh, yeah. Um...</i>

19:02.500 --> 19:04.890
<i>the Bill Nye guy you love was on TV.</i>

19:04.915 --> 19:07.578
<i>- I just thought of you.
- Oh. Okay.</i>

19:09.164 --> 19:11.031
Well, uh, we're in Las Vegas,

19:11.826 --> 19:14.234
but I'm keeping my phone on me, okay?

19:14.259 --> 19:16.625
- If you need anything.
<i>- Okay.</i>

19:20.761 --> 19:22.625
So your heat's back on? It's all good?

19:27.820 --> 19:29.695
<i>Yeah. Um, I'm sorry.</i>

19:29.720 --> 19:31.414
<i>It's hard to call when my mom's around.</i>

19:32.179 --> 19:34.289
We just want to make sure
that you're safe

19:34.314 --> 19:35.948
and you're well taken care of.

19:37.592 --> 19:38.998
<i>- Deja?
- (TRAFFIC PASSING)</i>

19:39.396 --> 19:40.703
Uh, we're making it work.

19:41.343 --> 19:42.414
Good.

19:43.486 --> 19:44.546
Yeah.

19:45.819 --> 19:47.820
I got to go. My mom's coming back.

19:48.007 --> 19:49.671
- Bye.
<i>- Bye.</i>

19:50.557 --> 19:51.835
♪

20:00.039 --> 20:01.148
Thank you.

20:01.938 --> 20:02.818
Hey.

20:02.843 --> 20:05.546
Hey, there he is! You
ready to hit the clurb?

20:06.054 --> 20:08.460
- (CHUCKLING)
- I think I'm gonna skip the clurb tonight.

20:08.485 --> 20:10.039
I'm feeling a little jet-lagged.

20:10.515 --> 20:13.203
But you go. Right?
Have fun with your friends.

20:13.421 --> 20:15.756
Get rowdy. You don't need
your brother-in-law

20:15.781 --> 20:17.343
weighing you down. I'll see you.

20:17.554 --> 20:20.222
("BRAND NEW WAY TO BE ME"
BY DAVID TOBIN PLAYING)

20:26.804 --> 20:28.515
♪ <i>I've got a shine</i> ♪

20:28.899 --> 20:31.921
♪ <i>Got a brand-new look about me</i> ♪

20:32.569 --> 20:34.781
- (WOMEN CHEERING)
- ♪ <i>A new peace of mind</i> ♪

20:34.905 --> 20:37.414
♪ <i>With a chill I've never known</i> ♪

20:38.757 --> 20:40.342
♪ <i>Planets so high</i> ♪

20:40.992 --> 20:43.046
- ♪ <i>Now revolve around me</i> ♪
- (SCREAMS)

20:44.214 --> 20:46.682
♪ <i>It's the new, it's the new</i> ♪

20:46.716 --> 20:51.578
♪ <i>It's the brand-new way to be me</i> ♪

20:54.117 --> 20:59.721
♪ <i>Brand-new way to be me</i> ♪

