Dad, the hens go right there,
so I'd chop your onion.

21:48.931 --> 21:50.507
- Okay. Yeah, I know. These are...
- REBECCA: Hi, guys.

21:50.532 --> 21:52.703
How's dinner looking? 'Cause
it's getting kind of late.

21:52.728 --> 21:55.343
My entree had to marinate
for three hours!

21:55.812 --> 21:59.476
- Okay, bud. Is this the one?
- Mom, this isn't the good china.

22:00.140 --> 22:01.726
This is going to be my seventh

22:01.751 --> 22:03.873
and final trip down to the basement.

22:03.898 --> 22:05.227
What else do you guys need?

22:05.262 --> 22:06.764
The Christmas lights,
the white pretty ones.

22:06.789 --> 22:08.197
Those are in the hallway closet.

22:08.609 --> 22:09.798
- Okay.
- I'll get them.

22:09.833 --> 22:11.960
And we need help
lighting all the candles.

22:12.796 --> 22:13.953
Okay.

22:14.476 --> 22:15.757
- Mom?
- Yes, babe.

22:15.782 --> 22:19.187
I think Dad should wear a tux,
and you should look like this.

22:20.449 --> 22:22.953
- (WOMEN CHEERING)
- (DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

22:25.335 --> 22:26.554
(BETH GIGGLES)

22:27.117 --> 22:30.119
Oh, my God, that was so fun! Thank you!

22:31.570 --> 22:32.955
Randall, what are you doing here?

22:33.351 --> 22:36.492
- Hey! No boys allowed. Strip or split.
- Yeah.

22:36.526 --> 22:39.023
- Yeah.
- I needed to talk to you.

22:39.383 --> 22:40.445
I didn't expect to see you

22:40.470 --> 22:41.960
getting your freak on with Magic Mike.

22:41.985 --> 22:45.843
His name is Anton, actually.
It's not important. What's up?

22:46.056 --> 22:47.156
Deja called.

22:47.671 --> 22:49.000
She did? Is everything okay?

22:49.025 --> 22:50.718
- No.
- What happened?

22:51.564 --> 22:52.960
Well, she said everything was okay,

22:52.985 --> 22:56.054
but she kept taking these long
pauses like it was Morse code.

22:56.629 --> 22:58.859
My parental bells rang hard, Beth.

22:59.597 --> 23:00.945
So nothing's wrong?

23:01.351 --> 23:04.242
Well, she said she was calling
just to check in on me,

23:04.267 --> 23:06.421
- but I think that...
- Oh, my God, Randall!

23:06.585 --> 23:08.171
You seriously crashed your sister's

23:08.196 --> 23:09.804
bachelorette party to tell me that?

23:09.829 --> 23:11.242
Beth, I know what this sounds like,

23:11.267 --> 23:12.882
- but my gut tells me...
- One night.

23:12.907 --> 23:15.242
You couldn't give me one night.

23:15.267 --> 23:18.912
I sit inside your anxiety every
damn minute of every damn day,

23:18.937 --> 23:20.836
- Excuse me, Beth.
- and you can't give me one night...

23:20.861 --> 23:23.101
I didn't realize that it was so
difficult being married to me.

23:23.126 --> 23:24.617
Hey, it's not always a party, husband.

23:24.642 --> 23:26.281
Well, I'll tell you something, wife.

23:26.370 --> 23:29.351
You know, I may lead with my
heart, but at least I've got...

23:29.716 --> 23:32.226
What? No. What? Say it.
You're gonna say I'm heartless?

23:32.251 --> 23:35.015
- No, not my words.
- No, because you said I was detached.

23:35.657 --> 23:37.437
You said I was the head,
and now you're trying to say

23:37.462 --> 23:40.109
I'm heartless because
I just want a break from this?

23:40.134 --> 23:42.039
- From all this?
- From all of this?

23:43.109 --> 23:44.510
You know what, Beth? You're right.

23:44.793 --> 23:46.085
The way that you're reacting

23:46.110 --> 23:48.218
to everything that's happened
is perfectly normal.

23:48.326 --> 23:49.459
You're all heart.

23:49.838 --> 23:52.156
I should've kept this
a "Deja-free zone,"

23:52.181 --> 23:54.215
as you so heartwarmingly called it.

23:54.499 --> 23:56.968
- It is what it is, right?
- You know what? Screw you!

23:56.993 --> 23:58.226
- RANDALL: Screw you, Beth.
- Oh, okay, okay, okay.

23:58.251 --> 24:00.500
Everybody take it easy.
Let's just take it easy.

24:00.525 --> 24:01.992
- Hey.
- Hey, please stay out of this.

24:02.017 --> 24:03.223
This is between me and Randall.

24:03.248 --> 24:04.523
This doesn't have anything
to do with you right now.

24:04.548 --> 24:07.039
I understand that. I...
But can you understand

24:07.064 --> 24:08.500
- where he's coming from?
- Please just sit back down,

24:08.525 --> 24:10.054
- all right?
- I'm not gonna sit down.

24:10.079 --> 24:11.898
Kate, this is not a Big Three moment.

24:11.923 --> 24:13.750
I know that, but he's my brother.

24:13.775 --> 24:15.640
- He's also my husband.
- Oh, I know.

24:15.755 --> 24:18.796
Randall has made it very clear
who's more important to him.

24:23.638 --> 24:25.289
I don't know why I just said that.

24:25.569 --> 24:27.023
I'm gonna get some air.

24:27.615 --> 24:28.812
Kate?

24:35.953 --> 24:37.093
- (BELL DINGS)
- Thank God!

24:37.118 --> 24:37.998
Okay, great.

24:38.023 --> 24:39.702
- So we're eating here?
- Yes, eat in here.

24:39.727 --> 24:41.061
- In here? Okay, great.
- I think we should.

24:41.096 --> 24:42.463
Oh, no!

24:42.497 --> 24:43.937
- JACK: What's wrong, Kev?
- REBECCA: What?

24:43.968 --> 24:45.678
Dad never turned the oven on!

24:45.703 --> 24:48.250
- I never what?
- Jack, really?

24:48.343 --> 24:50.491
Well, I had to go wash my hands

24:50.516 --> 24:51.984
- 'cause he had me cutting the onions.
- Oh, no.

24:52.018 --> 24:54.000
- I forgot. I'm sorry.
- No, it's ruined!

24:54.025 --> 24:56.593
Kev, I will cook that and we
can eat it tomorrow.

24:56.618 --> 24:59.520
(CRYING): No, now we're never,
never gonna have dinner,

25:00.258 --> 25:02.148
and you're gonna divorce him!

25:02.437 --> 25:04.062
- What?
- What?

25:04.480 --> 25:06.656
Sophie's parents are getting divorced.

25:06.799 --> 25:09.648
And you guys don't even want
to celebrate your anniversary.

25:09.921 --> 25:12.068
- Oh.
- So you're probably getting divorced, too.

25:12.093 --> 25:13.639
- No, no, no, we're...
- No, Kev, we're not.

25:13.664 --> 25:14.859
- Kevin, come here.
- Okay?

25:14.884 --> 25:17.890
Kevin, no, your dad and I
are not getting divorced.

25:17.958 --> 25:20.140
- No?
- No, never, ever.

25:20.165 --> 25:23.070
- Look at me. Never.
- Really?

25:23.227 --> 25:24.578
- Yeah.
- Never.

25:24.765 --> 25:26.101
Oh. Okay.

25:26.126 --> 25:27.921
Um, we're gonna go to bed now!

25:27.946 --> 25:29.031
Good night.

25:30.401 --> 25:32.515
- Come on!
- What?

25:34.882 --> 25:37.429
- (SLOT MACHINE CHIMES)
- What? Come on!

25:37.454 --> 25:38.835
Oh. Oh, you know what?

25:39.500 --> 25:41.268
Gonna give you that. Thank you.

25:41.481 --> 25:42.617
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

25:42.787 --> 25:43.906
RANDALL: Kate?

25:46.312 --> 25:47.343
You found me.

25:47.482 --> 25:48.812
It wasn't very hard.

25:49.211 --> 25:52.480
Only person still
drinking Cosmos in 2018.

25:54.681 --> 25:57.789
Carrie Bradshaw...
that girl is timeless,

25:58.263 --> 26:00.210
okay, and so are her favorite cocktails.

26:00.235 --> 26:01.476
Right. (CHUCKLES)

26:04.025 --> 26:05.335
Are you and Beth okay?

26:06.151 --> 26:07.374
Oh, we'll be fine.

26:07.795 --> 26:10.062
We have a blow-out like this
every few years.

26:10.305 --> 26:13.203
Never surrounded by
so much greased-up man meat,

26:13.228 --> 26:15.617
but, you know,
first time for everything.

26:17.374 --> 26:19.296
She wanted to make sure you were okay.

26:24.334 --> 26:27.882
I just want you to know, okay,
that I like to pride myself

26:28.044 --> 26:29.843
on being the first person to realize

26:29.868 --> 26:32.203
that Randall Pearson
was the coolest human ever.

26:32.548 --> 26:34.328
<i>I've known that since we were kids.</i>

26:34.565 --> 26:37.820
<i>You know, everyone thinks that
it was always Kevin and Kate.</i>

26:38.252 --> 26:39.853
<i>But the year after Dad died,</i>

26:40.050 --> 26:42.406
it was Kate and Randall

26:42.546 --> 26:45.507
eating Hot Pockets and watching
Mom pretending to be okay.

26:45.687 --> 26:47.020
<i>And binge-watching Sex and the City</i>

26:47.054 --> 26:48.960
<i>when binge-watching wasn't even a thing.</i>

26:49.382 --> 26:52.162
<i>And I knew that one day
that I was gonna lose you</i>

26:52.187 --> 26:54.210
<i>to somebody who was as cool as Beth.</i>

26:54.914 --> 26:57.070
But that someday... it happened so fast.

26:58.065 --> 27:01.396
And, God, she is spectacular.
I-I get it, I know it.

27:01.421 --> 27:04.531
But then, when I did,
when I lost you, I...

27:04.556 --> 27:08.025
First off, you can never lose me.

27:08.445 --> 27:09.750
Not even if you tried.

27:10.234 --> 27:12.278
You basically got brother LoJack on me.

27:12.531 --> 27:16.405
Okay? Kate, I was
a straight, black teenage boy.

27:16.430 --> 27:19.406
Do you really think I liked watching
<i>Sex and the City</i> that much?

27:20.457 --> 27:21.781
(BOTH LAUGHING)

27:22.818 --> 27:25.984
I just watched it because <i>you</i> loved it.

27:26.795 --> 27:28.335
- Really?
- Yeah.

27:29.925 --> 27:32.437
(SCOFFS) I thought
that you were such a Miranda.

27:33.129 --> 27:34.203
- (LAUGHS)
- Okay, okay.

27:34.228 --> 27:36.039
All right, all right. Enough. Whoa.

27:36.454 --> 27:38.742
I'm not crying at
my bachelorette party, again.

27:38.767 --> 27:39.984
That's my bad.

27:43.323 --> 27:44.570
So how is Toby?

27:45.531 --> 27:46.781
Uh, did you guys, like, bond?

27:46.806 --> 27:48.171
Did you, um, do the secret handshake?

27:48.196 --> 27:50.007
'Cause I think he really wants
a secret handshake.

27:50.494 --> 27:52.570
(LAUGHS) What? No. We... I just...

27:52.651 --> 27:54.187
We left him with his friends.

27:56.520 --> 27:57.757
(SIGHS) Okay.

27:58.076 --> 27:59.132
What?

28:01.171 --> 28:03.148
It's just that
his friends were the fillers.

28:04.445 --> 28:06.937
And he just wanted this weekend

28:06.962 --> 28:10.598
to be about, you know,
you and Kevin, and...

28:16.203 --> 28:18.265
- Hey, man.
- Uh, hey.

28:19.645 --> 28:22.156
I thought you guys had
gone to bed or something.

28:22.593 --> 28:24.718
Yeah, about that. We, uh...

28:25.314 --> 28:27.531
- We're sorry we bailed on you tonight.
- Right.

28:27.556 --> 28:29.070
Honestly, we didn't think you'd miss us.

28:29.147 --> 28:32.429
Oh, honestly, I didn't, so...

28:36.379 --> 28:38.632
- Want to go for a walk?
- Yeah, let me get my jacket.

28:42.196 --> 28:43.449
- (BELL DINGS)
- Yes.

28:45.309 --> 28:46.566
(JACK CLEARS THROAT)

28:46.719 --> 28:48.954
Ugh. No, I am way too tired

28:48.979 --> 28:50.512
to sit at the table and eat right now.

28:50.537 --> 28:51.856
Why don't you just put it out,

28:51.881 --> 28:54.035
and I'll come back downstairs
and wrap it up later.

28:54.060 --> 28:57.543
Yeah, I'm just gonna let it
cool off a little bit.

29:00.101 --> 29:03.059
Wow. I mean, they really did try.

29:03.084 --> 29:04.818
- Yeah. (CHUCKLES)
- I mean...

29:04.954 --> 29:07.160
Got to work on
the follow-through, but...

29:07.619 --> 29:10.254
Well, it's hard to live up
to your standard. It is.

29:12.925 --> 29:14.348
- Hey, babe?
- Mm-hmm.

29:15.516 --> 29:17.817
I really missed
giving you a gift this year.

29:17.842 --> 29:19.262
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

29:19.762 --> 29:21.356
Even if it wasn't gonna be as great

29:21.381 --> 29:23.027
as the one you would have given me.

29:25.652 --> 29:26.957
I'm sorry for...

29:28.185 --> 29:30.004
de-Jacking you.

29:30.821 --> 29:31.981
De-Jacking me?

29:32.006 --> 29:33.090
(LAUGHS)

29:34.668 --> 29:35.910
- Yeah.
- Yes?

29:35.989 --> 29:37.277
- Hey.
- Yeah.

29:37.515 --> 29:40.074
- Let's never do nothing again.
- No. Yeah.

29:40.500 --> 29:41.777
- Deal?
- Deal.

29:48.872 --> 29:50.559
Come on, let's go upstairs.

30:01.184 --> 30:02.582
What? Jack.

30:02.607 --> 30:03.723
- No...
- Is this you?

30:03.748 --> 30:05.535
No, this is not me, I swear.

30:05.882 --> 30:07.027
(CHUCKLES): I swear.

30:09.593 --> 30:10.723
What is that?

30:13.597 --> 30:14.762
"Mom and Dad."

30:18.769 --> 30:20.621
"Dear Mom and Dad, go out on the roof,

30:20.646 --> 30:24.549
lie down, look up, hold hands
and wait. Love, the Big Three."

30:24.574 --> 30:25.809
- "Meteor shower."
- Oh.

30:25.834 --> 30:26.905
(LAUGHS)

30:26.930 --> 30:28.238
Well, you did it, babe.

30:29.001 --> 30:31.645
- You created mini yous.
- We did.

30:32.115 --> 30:33.332
You did.

30:34.649 --> 30:35.996
Look at this.

30:46.003 --> 30:48.410
Madison is drunk snoring
in my room. (CHUCKLES)

30:49.379 --> 30:51.051
Who knew that such a loud sound

30:51.076 --> 30:52.754
could come from such a tiny person?

30:55.234 --> 30:58.043
- Can I come in?
- Sure.

30:59.145 --> 31:00.348
(TV PLAYING QUIETLY)

31:03.914 --> 31:05.066
(TV TURNS OFF)

31:05.163 --> 31:08.866
Oh, when I'm upset, I eat candy.
And when I'm drunk.

31:10.111 --> 31:11.262
I didn't know that.

31:12.423 --> 31:13.606
(CLEARS THROAT)

31:14.916 --> 31:16.918
It's really hard for me to make friends.

31:18.711 --> 31:20.387
My brothers were my friends.

31:20.684 --> 31:23.426
I was always, um, self-conscious

31:23.474 --> 31:24.621
and, um...

31:25.371 --> 31:28.535
defensive around strong women.

31:28.560 --> 31:31.043
I mean, look no further than my mother.

31:33.636 --> 31:37.906
And so when Randall met you,
I was, I was intimidated.

31:38.879 --> 31:40.871
Intimidated? Why?

31:42.941 --> 31:44.301
Because you're flawless.

31:44.399 --> 31:45.988
Because when I was a waitress,

31:46.366 --> 31:49.215
you were getting a master's
and building a house.

31:50.400 --> 31:53.668
And then you...
you have a meaningful job.

31:53.693 --> 31:56.270
You bought a building
and you foster kids.

31:56.295 --> 31:58.910
And I-I sing and I-I adopted a dog.

32:00.082 --> 32:01.379
Kate... (SCOFFS)

32:02.456 --> 32:04.824
Man, I am so far

32:05.559 --> 32:08.043
from doing what I actually want to do

32:08.068 --> 32:11.777
in my job that I agreed to buy
a building with your brother,

32:11.863 --> 32:13.973
which is exhausting.

32:14.441 --> 32:17.629
And that is nothing
compared to fostering,

32:17.654 --> 32:22.692
which is the hardest thing
I have ever done in my life.

32:24.802 --> 32:27.152
And I went and got myself
attached to this little girl,

32:27.177 --> 32:28.520
and now she's gone.

32:29.888 --> 32:30.981
And...

32:32.498 --> 32:34.668
I've been trying not to think about her,

32:36.270 --> 32:38.176
but it's... I can't. It's like...

32:41.011 --> 32:43.457
I just keep wondering, like,
is she okay, you know?

32:43.482 --> 32:44.645
Is she cold?

32:45.876 --> 32:47.106
Is she stressed?

32:49.304 --> 32:52.879
Does her science teacher
know how smart she is?

32:53.741 --> 32:54.973
Oh, Beth.

32:56.416 --> 32:57.785
I'm sorry.

32:58.313 --> 32:59.785
I'm so sorry.

33:00.081 --> 33:01.379
Such is life.

33:07.424 --> 33:10.348
So I-I had this whole new plan
for my life, you know,

33:11.449 --> 33:12.824
and for my career, actually.

33:12.849 --> 33:15.316
And then the movie fell apart,
then the plan fell apart,

33:15.341 --> 33:18.113
so I don't want to talk
about it anymore.

33:18.487 --> 33:19.676
Randall, you go.

33:20.490 --> 33:24.035
Uh... I got to let go of Deja.

33:25.301 --> 33:27.090
I got to move on, mentally,

33:27.115 --> 33:29.746
and not put it on my wife
to be the only strong one.

33:30.760 --> 33:32.215
You came up with that all by yourself?

33:32.240 --> 33:33.785
Listen, man, he... that's his thing.

33:33.810 --> 33:35.621
He does that. What about you?

33:36.121 --> 33:38.691
Whew. I'm just wondering if it
was worth dropping a few grand

33:38.716 --> 33:41.160
to fly three strangers out here
so I didn't look lame

33:41.185 --> 33:43.043
in front of my future brothers-in-law.

33:47.514 --> 33:49.816
- You guys know I have a brother?
- No.

33:51.106 --> 33:53.340
Yeah. He, uh, couldn't
make it this weekend.

33:53.365 --> 33:54.973
I doubt he even tried.

33:56.277 --> 34:00.623
I was ten when he was born,
so I adored the kid since birth.

34:00.657 --> 34:02.832
I-I remember, I was 16,
I was such a nerd.

34:02.857 --> 34:03.941
I was like a...

34:03.966 --> 34:07.035
like a Dungeons & Dragons
by myself kind of nerd.

34:07.060 --> 34:07.793
Ugh.

34:07.818 --> 34:09.315
You do not want to
know what it feels like

34:09.341 --> 34:13.139
to be a 16-year-old when
your six-year-old brother says

34:13.164 --> 34:15.431
he doesn't want
to play with you anymore.

34:15.610 --> 34:17.440
And you know that he means it.

34:19.974 --> 34:22.996
Look, I'm sorry I brought
you guys all this way

34:23.021 --> 34:24.262
with everything you got going on.

34:24.286 --> 34:26.598
I just got excited about
having a second chance at...

34:27.676 --> 34:29.340
two new brothers, you know?

34:31.379 --> 34:32.434
I wanted to impress you,

34:32.458 --> 34:35.534
and not-and not just because
my gal loves you,

34:35.560 --> 34:37.706
but because you guys
impress the hell out of me.

34:43.110 --> 34:44.237
Kevin Costner.

34:45.762 --> 34:47.895
Kevin Costner was cut out of
<i>The Big Chill.</i>

34:48.022 --> 34:50.996
Four years later, he went on
to star in <i>The Untouchables</i>

34:51.021 --> 34:53.190
with Connery, Garcia and De Niro.

34:53.715 --> 34:55.340
Do you have Ron Howard's phone number

34:55.364 --> 34:56.895
in that fancy phone of yours?

34:57.787 --> 34:58.793
Yeah.

34:59.319 --> 35:01.053
- Call him.
- No.

35:01.252 --> 35:02.520
- Y-Yeah.
- No.

35:02.703 --> 35:05.402
You call him,
and you tell him he has made

35:05.427 --> 35:08.566
a <i>Pretty Woman</i> sized mistake. Big.

35:08.959 --> 35:10.895
Huge. All right?

35:10.920 --> 35:13.387
Y-You-You thank him for the opportunity,

35:13.887 --> 35:16.824
but you let him know that it's his loss.

35:16.953 --> 35:19.426
You make him believe it
because you believe it.

35:19.847 --> 35:21.645
- Now, Randy. Can I call you Randy?
- No.

35:21.670 --> 35:25.066
Okay. I'm not gonna give you
any advice about Deja.

35:26.110 --> 35:29.762
But know this: if you, Randall Pearson,

35:29.787 --> 35:32.051
are beating yourself up about anything,

35:32.215 --> 35:33.965
then the rest of the world
should collectively

35:33.990 --> 35:35.387
be jumping in front of a train.

35:42.914 --> 35:44.309
You gonna be good to our sister?

35:45.105 --> 35:46.238
Of course I will.

35:47.488 --> 35:48.973
Welcome to the family, brother.

35:49.366 --> 35:51.109
- (GROWLS): Yeah. Awesome.
- (LAUGHTER)

35:53.495 --> 35:55.320
All right, so two
takeaways from tonight.

35:55.345 --> 35:56.149
Mm-hmm.

35:56.174 --> 35:58.918
- Uh, Cornish hens are delicious.
- God, so good.

35:58.943 --> 36:01.996
And I'm pretty sure that Kevin's
gonna be a famous chef one day.

36:02.021 --> 36:03.231
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

36:03.340 --> 36:04.474
(BOTH LAUGH)

36:04.657 --> 36:05.809
I mean...

36:07.035 --> 36:08.652
Hey, do you want to hear
what Randall told me

36:08.677 --> 36:10.449
about meteor showers?

36:10.788 --> 36:14.145
- Yeah, I do.
- Well, he kind of told me a lot.

36:14.723 --> 36:17.199
- Like, a lot. (LAUGHS)
- (LAUGHS) Of course.

36:17.292 --> 36:20.427
But what he told me, at least the...

36:21.606 --> 36:23.027
the part that I understood,

36:23.770 --> 36:27.027
was that meteors are always up there,

36:27.570 --> 36:29.043
whizzing around.

36:29.689 --> 36:31.991
We just... we never notice them.

36:32.723 --> 36:33.879
REBECCA: Hmm.

36:34.496 --> 36:37.582
It's only once in a while
that we actually see one.

36:38.488 --> 36:39.824
You know, see...

36:40.374 --> 36:43.145
just how spectacular they really are.

36:45.575 --> 36:46.737
Wow.

36:51.260 --> 36:52.902
- Hey, Bec?
- Yeah.

36:54.745 --> 36:56.809
I don't need anniversaries to see you.

36:57.891 --> 36:59.238
I see you every day.

37:00.176 --> 37:03.426
You are my daily meteor shower.

37:03.892 --> 37:06.496
Ah, babe.

37:08.410 --> 37:09.863
Thank you for marrying me.

37:10.750 --> 37:12.473
Mm. Thank you for asking me.

37:17.187 --> 37:19.231
("SEDONA" BY HOUNDMOUTH PLAYING)

37:23.669 --> 37:25.270
(REBECCA SIGHS, CHUCKLES)

37:26.716 --> 37:28.738
YOUNG KEVIN: <i>Hey, Dad,
could I ask you something?</i>

37:29.293 --> 37:31.098
Do you think the hens are big enough?

37:32.807 --> 37:34.449
It's not about the hens, kiddo.

37:36.326 --> 37:38.777
A big, grand gesture... it's not about

37:39.324 --> 37:41.291
the actual thing that you do.

37:41.467 --> 37:43.348
RANDALL: Tobias, may I present

37:43.455 --> 37:45.122
seedy old Vegas.

37:45.514 --> 37:46.504
(LAUGHING)

37:46.529 --> 37:48.746
♪ <i>Right smack on top</i> ♪

37:51.162 --> 37:53.746
♪ <i>Of Sedona Arabelle...</i> ♪

37:53.771 --> 37:57.551
It's not about what you say,
it's about intent.

37:57.981 --> 37:59.135
(GASPS) Oh!

37:59.160 --> 38:00.561
- Whoa.
- Wow.

38:00.586 --> 38:02.840
- REBECCA: Did you see that one?
- (LAUGHS) Yeah.

38:02.967 --> 38:05.348
It's about taking the time
to tell the person

38:05.373 --> 38:08.895
you care about, "I see you. I hear you.

38:10.422 --> 38:11.754
♪ <i>Whoa, whoa...</i> ♪

38:12.070 --> 38:14.543
<i>"I know exactly what you need right now,</i>

38:15.928 --> 38:18.363
<i>and I'm showing how important
that is to me."</i>

38:20.830 --> 38:23.277
Never hurts to have
a couple of big-ass hens.

38:23.508 --> 38:26.590
(CHUCKLES) No, it never hurts
to have a couple big-ass hens.

38:31.761 --> 38:34.527
♪ <i>Hey there, Sedona,</i>
<i>let me cut you a deal</i> ♪

38:34.552 --> 38:36.086
♪ <i>I'm a little hungover</i> ♪

38:36.111 --> 38:38.646
♪ <i>And I may have to steal your soul...</i> ♪

38:38.802 --> 38:39.934
(LINE RINGING)

38:40.110 --> 38:42.078
RON HOWARD: <i>Hey, Kevin,
how the hell are ya?</i>

38:42.605 --> 38:43.746
Ron... uh...

38:44.824 --> 38:46.675
Uh, first of all, obviously,
thank you for the opportunity,

38:46.709 --> 38:48.152
but I'm telling you, it was wrong

38:48.177 --> 38:50.324
to cut me out of the movie.
Okay? It's special.

38:50.349 --> 38:53.152
I'm telling you, I can
feel it in my gut, it's special.

38:53.177 --> 38:54.270
And even if I'm wrong,
you know, you could've

38:54.295 --> 38:55.785
picked up the phone,
you could've called me.

38:55.810 --> 38:58.111
<i>I would expect that
common courtesy from you.</i>

38:58.525 --> 39:00.910
- You done?
- Yeah.

39:02.317 --> 39:04.285
Obviously, you've heard that the movie

39:04.310 --> 39:07.191
could not sustain
the weight of a romance.

39:07.863 --> 39:10.621
<i>But I didn't cut you out
of the movie, Kevin.</i>

39:11.023 --> 39:13.824
<i>Your work with Sly is truly remarkable.</i>

39:13.849 --> 39:16.879
I mean the father/son
story <i>is</i> the movie.

39:18.274 --> 39:20.442
Truthfully, this might be
one of the best things

39:20.476 --> 39:21.598
that I've ever done.

39:21.762 --> 39:23.730
- That's why I didn't call you.
- Oh.

39:24.046 --> 39:25.824
- Well, that's, you know...
<i>- Kevin,</i>

39:26.410 --> 39:29.051
just take care of yourself
and be healthy.

39:30.324 --> 39:33.402
And... you might want to think about

39:33.427 --> 39:35.535
going ahead and buying
yourself a tuxedo.

39:35.842 --> 39:37.168
A tux. Okay. (CHUCKLES)

39:38.059 --> 39:39.152
<i>Talk soon.</i>

39:39.907 --> 39:41.910
♪ <i>And you shot the plot,</i>
<i>and I remember...</i> ♪

39:41.974 --> 39:43.113
Ron, thank you.

39:45.660 --> 39:46.770
Thank you, Ron.

39:46.795 --> 39:49.801
- ♪ <i>So bright and pink</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>So bright and pink</i> ♪

39:50.955 --> 39:55.215
♪ <i>Saturday night kind of pink.</i> ♪

40:00.691 --> 40:02.902
It's not fair of me to keep
putting you in a position

40:02.927 --> 40:04.410
where you have to be the realist.

40:05.934 --> 40:08.402
We made a decision about Deja,
the both of us,

40:08.670 --> 40:11.246
and now I'm questioning it, and...

40:12.360 --> 40:13.668
it's not fair.

40:15.598 --> 40:17.199
I love that you're all heart.

40:18.207 --> 40:19.684
I married you for your heart.

40:20.224 --> 40:21.902
And your abs, but mostly your heart.

40:24.259 --> 40:25.465
(BETH CHUCKLES)

40:28.934 --> 40:30.652
We did what we thought was right.

40:32.502 --> 40:34.277
And I can't keep bringing it up,

40:34.511 --> 40:35.808
bringing it all back.

40:37.593 --> 40:38.754
I'm sorry.

40:39.861 --> 40:41.332
It's time to move forward.

40:47.785 --> 40:50.262
Excuse me, can you make
this left up here, please?

40:50.990 --> 40:52.082
Thanks.

40:55.147 --> 40:57.113
I think I'm gonna be the heart today.

41:05.246 --> 41:07.426
- You looking for Shauna?
- Uh, yes, ma'am.

41:07.543 --> 41:08.943
She doesn't live here anymore.

